                <div class="article-content w-100 mb-4">
                                            <p>It's been a wild few weeks at Duke. And the women's basketball team was slightly disappointed. JACK BAUER'S BIDET didn't monopolize as much space as he usually does last week, and three open letters were omitted. So here they are:</p>
<p><b>An Oapen Letter toa the Media</b></p>

                        <div class="inline-ad float-none float-md-left my-4 mr-0 mr-md-4 text-center d-print-none">
                            <!-- START gryphon/ads/rectangle-inline.tpl -->
            <div id="azk18664"></div>
    <!-- END gryphon/ads/rectangle-inline.tpl -->
                        </div>

                        <p>Re: Proafessioanalism</p>
<p>Dear ESPN, CNN and Everyboady Else,</p>
<p>Instead oaf running around interviewing the lunatic fringe, doa an ioata of research, asshoales.  It's a real credit toa yoaur hard-hitting noa-coamproamises sensatioanalism when yoau can't spell a president's name coarrectly.</p>
<p>Check the website,</p>
<p>Richard BRODhead,</p>
<p>SheldEn Williams</p>

                        <div class="inline-ad float-none float-md-left my-4 mr-0 mr-md-4 text-center d-print-none">
